2029 Instruction *InstCombinerImpl::foldSelectExtConst(SelectInst &Sel) {
2030  Constant *C;
2031  if (!match(Sel.getTrueValue(), m_Constant(C)) &&
2032  !match(Sel.getFalseValue(), m_Constant(C)))
2033  return nullptr;
2034 
2035  Instruction *ExtInst;
2036  if (!match(Sel.getTrueValue(), m_Instruction(ExtInst)) &&
2037  !match(Sel.getFalseValue(), m_Instruction(ExtInst)))
2038  return nullptr;
2039 
2040  auto ExtOpcode = ExtInst->getOpcode();
2041  if (ExtOpcode != Instruction::ZExt && ExtOpcode != Instruction::SExt)
2042  return nullptr;
2043 
2044  // If we are extending from a boolean type or if we can create a select that
2045  // has the same size operands as its condition, try to narrow the select.
2046  Value *X = ExtInst->getOperand(0);
2047  Type *SmallType = X->getType();
2048  Value *Cond = Sel.getCondition();
2049  auto *Cmp = dyn_cast<CmpInst>(Cond);
2050  if (!SmallType->isIntOrIntVectorTy(1) &&
2051  (!Cmp || Cmp->getOperand(0)->getType() != SmallType))
2052  return nullptr;
2053 
2054  // If the constant is the same after truncation to the smaller type and
2055  // extension to the original type, we can narrow the select.
2056  Type *SelType = Sel.getType();
2057  Constant *TruncC = ConstantExpr::getTrunc(C, SmallType);
2058  Constant *ExtC = ConstantExpr::getCast(ExtOpcode, TruncC, SelType);
2059  if (ExtC == C && ExtInst->hasOneUse()) {
2060  Value *TruncCVal = cast<Value>(TruncC);
2061  if (ExtInst == Sel.getFalseValue())
2062  std::swap(X, TruncCVal);
2063 
2064  // select Cond, (ext X), C --> ext(select Cond, X, C')
2065  // select Cond, C, (ext X) --> ext(select Cond, C', X)
2066  Value *NewSel = Builder.CreateSelect(Cond, X, TruncCVal, "narrow", &Sel);
2067  return CastInst::Create(Instruction::CastOps(ExtOpcode), NewSel, SelType);
2068  }
2069 
2070  // If one arm of the select is the extend of the condition, replace that arm
2071  // with the extension of the appropriate known bool value.
2072  if (Cond == X) {
2073  if (ExtInst == Sel.getTrueValue()) {
2074  // select X, (sext X), C --> select X, -1, C
2075  // select X, (zext X), C --> select X, 1, C
2076  Constant *One = ConstantInt::getTrue(SmallType);
2077  Constant *AllOnesOrOne = ConstantExpr::getCast(ExtOpcode, One, SelType);
2078  return SelectInst::Create(Cond, AllOnesOrOne, C, "", nullptr, &Sel);
2079  } else {
2080  // select X, C, (sext X) --> select X, C, 0
2081  // select X, C, (zext X) --> select X, C, 0
2082  Constant *Zero = ConstantInt::getNullValue(SelType);
2083  return SelectInst::Create(Cond, C, Zero, "", nullptr, &Sel);
2084  }
2085  }
2086 
2087  return nullptr;
2088 }

2090 /// Try to transform a vector select with a constant condition vector into a
2091 /// shuffle for easier combining with other shuffles and insert/extract.
2092 static Instruction *canonicalizeSelectToShuffle(SelectInst &SI) {
2093  Value *CondVal = SI.getCondition();
2094  Constant *CondC;
2095  auto *CondValTy = dyn_cast<FixedVectorType>(CondVal->getType());
2096  if (!CondValTy || !match(CondVal, m_Constant(CondC)))
2097  return nullptr;
2098 
2099  unsigned NumElts = CondValTy->getNumElements();
2100  SmallVector<int, 16> Mask;
2101  Mask.reserve(NumElts);
2102  for (unsigned i = 0; i != NumElts; ++i) {
2103  Constant *Elt = CondC->getAggregateElement(i);
2104  if (!Elt)
2105  return nullptr;
2106 
2107  if (Elt->isOneValue()) {
2108  // If the select condition element is true, choose from the 1st vector.
2109  Mask.push_back(i);
2110  } else if (Elt->isNullValue()) {
2111  // If the select condition element is false, choose from the 2nd vector.
2112  Mask.push_back(i + NumElts);
2113  } else if (isa<UndefValue>(Elt)) {
2114  // Undef in a select condition (choose one of the operands) does not mean
2115  // the same thing as undef in a shuffle mask (any value is acceptable), so
2116  // give up.
2117  return nullptr;
2118  } else {
2119  // Bail out on a constant expression.
2120  return nullptr;
2121  }
2122  }
2123 
2124  return new ShuffleVectorInst(SI.getTrueValue(), SI.getFalseValue(), Mask);
2125 }

2127 /// If we have a select of vectors with a scalar condition, try to convert that
2128 /// to a vector select by splatting the condition. A splat may get folded with
2129 /// other operations in IR and having all operands of a select be vector types
2130 /// is likely better for vector codegen.
2131 static Instruction *canonicalizeScalarSelectOfVecs(SelectInst &Sel,
2132  InstCombinerImpl &IC) {
2133  auto *Ty = dyn_cast<VectorType>(Sel.getType());
2134  if (!Ty)
2135  return nullptr;
2136 
2137  // We can replace a single-use extract with constant index.
2138  Value *Cond = Sel.getCondition();
2139  if (!match(Cond, m_OneUse(m_ExtractElt(m_Value(), m_ConstantInt()))))
2140  return nullptr;
2141 
2142  // select (extelt V, Index), T, F --> select (splat V, Index), T, F
2143  // Splatting the extracted condition reduces code (we could directly create a
2144  // splat shuffle of the source vector to eliminate the intermediate step).
2145  return IC.replaceOperand(
2146  Sel, 0, IC.Builder.CreateVectorSplat(Ty->getElementCount(), Cond));
2147 }

2149 /// Reuse bitcasted operands between a compare and select:
2150 /// select (cmp (bitcast C), (bitcast D)), (bitcast' C), (bitcast' D) -->
2151 /// bitcast (select (cmp (bitcast C), (bitcast D)), (bitcast C), (bitcast D))
2152 static Instruction *foldSelectCmpBitcasts(SelectInst &Sel,
2153  InstCombiner::BuilderTy &Builder) {
2154  Value *Cond = Sel.getCondition();
2155  Value *TVal = Sel.getTrueValue();
2156  Value *FVal = Sel.getFalseValue();
2157 
2158  CmpInst::Predicate Pred;
2159  Value *A, *B;
2160  if (!match(Cond, m_Cmp(Pred, m_Value(A), m_Value(B))))
2161  return nullptr;
2162 
2163  // The select condition is a compare instruction. If the select's true/false
2164  // values are already the same as the compare operands, there's nothing to do.
2165  if (TVal == A || TVal == B || FVal == A || FVal == B)
2166  return nullptr;
2167 
2168  Value *C, *D;
2169  if (!match(A, m_BitCast(m_Value(C))) || !match(B, m_BitCast(m_Value(D))))
2170  return nullptr;
2171 
2172  // select (cmp (bitcast C), (bitcast D)), (bitcast TSrc), (bitcast FSrc)
2173  Value *TSrc, *FSrc;
2174  if (!match(TVal, m_BitCast(m_Value(TSrc))) ||
2175  !match(FVal, m_BitCast(m_Value(FSrc))))
2176  return nullptr;
2177 
2178  // If the select true/false values are *different bitcasts* of the same source
2179  // operands, make the select operands the same as the compare operands and
2180  // cast the result. This is the canonical select form for min/max.
2181  Value *NewSel;
2182  if (TSrc == C && FSrc == D) {
2183  // select (cmp (bitcast C), (bitcast D)), (bitcast' C), (bitcast' D) -->
2184  // bitcast (select (cmp A, B), A, B)
2185  NewSel = Builder.CreateSelect(Cond, A, B, "", &Sel);
2186  } else if (TSrc == D && FSrc == C) {
2187  // select (cmp (bitcast C), (bitcast D)), (bitcast' D), (bitcast' C) -->
2188  // bitcast (select (cmp A, B), B, A)
2189  NewSel = Builder.CreateSelect(Cond, B, A, "", &Sel);
2190  } else {
2191  return nullptr;
2192  }
2193  return CastInst::CreateBitOrPointerCast(NewSel, Sel.getType());
2194 }

2196 /// Try to eliminate select instructions that test the returned flag of cmpxchg
2197 /// instructions.
2198 ///
2199 /// If a select instruction tests the returned flag of a cmpxchg instruction and
2200 /// selects between the returned value of the cmpxchg instruction its compare
2201 /// operand, the result of the select will always be equal to its false value.
2202 /// For example:
2203 ///
2204 /// %0 = cmpxchg i64* %ptr, i64 %compare, i64 %new_value seq_cst seq_cst
2205 /// %1 = extractvalue { i64, i1 } %0, 1
2206 /// %2 = extractvalue { i64, i1 } %0, 0
2207 /// %3 = select i1 %1, i64 %compare, i64 %2
2208 /// ret i64 %3
2209 ///
2210 /// The returned value of the cmpxchg instruction (%2) is the original value
2211 /// located at %ptr prior to any update. If the cmpxchg operation succeeds, %2
2212 /// must have been equal to %compare. Thus, the result of the select is always
2213 /// equal to %2, and the code can be simplified to:
2214 ///
2215 /// %0 = cmpxchg i64* %ptr, i64 %compare, i64 %new_value seq_cst seq_cst
2216 /// %1 = extractvalue { i64, i1 } %0, 0
2217 /// ret i64 %1
2218 ///
2219 static Value *foldSelectCmpXchg(SelectInst &SI) {
2220  // A helper that determines if V is an extractvalue instruction whose
2221  // aggregate operand is a cmpxchg instruction and whose single index is equal
2222  // to I. If such conditions are true, the helper returns the cmpxchg
2223  // instruction; otherwise, a nullptr is returned.
2224  auto isExtractFromCmpXchg = [](Value *V, unsigned I) -> AtomicCmpXchgInst * {
2225  auto *Extract = dyn_cast<ExtractValueInst>(V);
2226  if (!Extract)
2227  return nullptr;
2228  if (Extract->getIndices()[0] != I)
2229  return nullptr;
2230  return dyn_cast<AtomicCmpXchgInst>(Extract->getAggregateOperand());
2231  };
2232 
2233  // If the select has a single user, and this user is a select instruction that
2234  // we can simplify, skip the cmpxchg simplification for now.
2235  if (SI.hasOneUse())
2236  if (auto *Select = dyn_cast<SelectInst>(SI.user_back()))
2237  if (Select->getCondition() == SI.getCondition())
2238  if (Select->getFalseValue() == SI.getTrueValue() ||
2239  Select->getTrueValue() == SI.getFalseValue())
2240  return nullptr;
2241 
2242  // Ensure the select condition is the returned flag of a cmpxchg instruction.
2243  auto *CmpXchg = isExtractFromCmpXchg(SI.getCondition(), 1);
2244  if (!CmpXchg)
2245  return nullptr;
2246 
2247  // Check the true value case: The true value of the select is the returned
2248  // value of the same cmpxchg used by the condition, and the false value is the
2249  // cmpxchg instruction's compare operand.
2250  if (auto *X = isExtractFromCmpXchg(SI.getTrueValue(), 0))
2251  if (X == CmpXchg && X->getCompareOperand() == SI.getFalseValue())
2252  return SI.getFalseValue();
2253 
2254  // Check the false value case: The false value of the select is the returned
2255  // value of the same cmpxchg used by the condition, and the true value is the
2256  // cmpxchg instruction's compare operand.
2257  if (auto *X = isExtractFromCmpXchg(SI.getFalseValue(), 0))
2258  if (X == CmpXchg && X->getCompareOperand() == SI.getTrueValue())
2259  return SI.getFalseValue();
2260 
2261  return nullptr;
2262 }

2264 /// Try to reduce a funnel/rotate pattern that includes a compare and select
2265 /// into a funnel shift intrinsic. Example:
2266 /// rotl32(a, b) --> (b == 0 ? a : ((a >> (32 - b)) | (a << b)))
2267 /// --> call llvm.fshl.i32(a, a, b)
2268 /// fshl32(a, b, c) --> (c == 0 ? a : ((b >> (32 - c)) | (a << c)))
2269 /// --> call llvm.fshl.i32(a, b, c)
2270 /// fshr32(a, b, c) --> (c == 0 ? b : ((a >> (32 - c)) | (b << c)))
2271 /// --> call llvm.fshr.i32(a, b, c)
2272 static Instruction *foldSelectFunnelShift(SelectInst &Sel,
2273  InstCombiner::BuilderTy &Builder) {
2274  // This must be a power-of-2 type for a bitmasking transform to be valid.
2275  unsigned Width = Sel.getType()->getScalarSizeInBits();
2276  if (!isPowerOf2_32(Width))
2277  return nullptr;
2278 
2279  BinaryOperator *Or0, *Or1;
2280  if (!match(Sel.getFalseValue(), m_OneUse(m_Or(m_BinOp(Or0), m_BinOp(Or1)))))
2281  return nullptr;
2282 
2283  Value *SV0, *SV1, *SA0, *SA1;
2284  if (!match(Or0, m_OneUse(m_LogicalShift(m_Value(SV0),
2285  m_ZExtOrSelf(m_Value(SA0))))) ||
2286  !match(Or1, m_OneUse(m_LogicalShift(m_Value(SV1),
2287  m_ZExtOrSelf(m_Value(SA1))))) ||
2288  Or0->getOpcode() == Or1->getOpcode())
2289  return nullptr;
2290 
2291  // Canonicalize to or(shl(SV0, SA0), lshr(SV1, SA1)).
2292  if (Or0->getOpcode() == BinaryOperator::LShr) {
2293  std::swap(Or0, Or1);
2294  std::swap(SV0, SV1);
2295  std::swap(SA0, SA1);
2296  }
2297  assert(Or0->getOpcode() == BinaryOperator::Shl &&
2298  Or1->getOpcode() == BinaryOperator::LShr &&
2299  "Illegal or(shift,shift) pair");
2300 
2301  // Check the shift amounts to see if they are an opposite pair.
2302  Value *ShAmt;
2303  if (match(SA1, m_OneUse(m_Sub(m_SpecificInt(Width), m_Specific(SA0)))))
2304  ShAmt = SA0;
2305  else if (match(SA0, m_OneUse(m_Sub(m_SpecificInt(Width), m_Specific(SA1)))))
2306  ShAmt = SA1;
2307  else
2308  return nullptr;
2309 
2310  // We should now have this pattern:
2311  // select ?, TVal, (or (shl SV0, SA0), (lshr SV1, SA1))
2312  // The false value of the select must be a funnel-shift of the true value:
2313  // IsFShl -> TVal must be SV0 else TVal must be SV1.
2314  bool IsFshl = (ShAmt == SA0);
2315  Value *TVal = Sel.getTrueValue();
2316  if ((IsFshl && TVal != SV0) || (!IsFshl && TVal != SV1))
2317  return nullptr;
2318 
2319  // Finally, see if the select is filtering out a shift-by-zero.
2320  Value *Cond = Sel.getCondition();
2321  ICmpInst::Predicate Pred;
2322  if (!match(Cond, m_OneUse(m_ICmp(Pred, m_Specific(ShAmt), m_ZeroInt()))) ||
2323  Pred != ICmpInst::ICMP_EQ)
2324  return nullptr;
2325 
2326  // If this is not a rotate then the select was blocking poison from the
2327  // 'shift-by-zero' non-TVal, but a funnel shift won't - so freeze it.
2328  if (SV0 != SV1) {
2329  if (IsFshl && !llvm::isGuaranteedNotToBePoison(SV1))
2330  SV1 = Builder.CreateFreeze(SV1);
2331  else if (!IsFshl && !llvm::isGuaranteedNotToBePoison(SV0))
2332  SV0 = Builder.CreateFreeze(SV0);
2333  }
2334 
2335  // This is a funnel/rotate that avoids shift-by-bitwidth UB in a suboptimal way.
2336  // Convert to funnel shift intrinsic.
2337  Intrinsic::ID IID = IsFshl ? Intrinsic::fshl : Intrinsic::fshr;
2338  Function *F = Intrinsic::getDeclaration(Sel.getModule(), IID, Sel.getType());
2339  ShAmt = Builder.CreateZExt(ShAmt, Sel.getType());
2340  return CallInst::Create(F, { SV0, SV1, ShAmt });
2341 }

2343 static Instruction *foldSelectToCopysign(SelectInst &Sel,
2344  InstCombiner::BuilderTy &Builder) {
2345  Value *Cond = Sel.getCondition();
2346  Value *TVal = Sel.getTrueValue();
2347  Value *FVal = Sel.getFalseValue();
2348  Type *SelType = Sel.getType();
2349 
2350  // Match select ?, TC, FC where the constants are equal but negated.
2351  // TODO: Generalize to handle a negated variable operand?
2352  const APFloat *TC, *FC;
2353  if (!match(TVal, m_APFloatAllowUndef(TC)) ||
2354  !match(FVal, m_APFloatAllowUndef(FC)) ||
2355  !abs(*TC).bitwiseIsEqual(abs(*FC)))
2356  return nullptr;
2357 
2358  assert(TC != FC && "Expected equal select arms to simplify");
2359 
2360  Value *X;
2361  const APInt *C;
2362  bool IsTrueIfSignSet;
2363  ICmpInst::Predicate Pred;
2364  if (!match(Cond, m_OneUse(m_ICmp(Pred, m_BitCast(m_Value(X)), m_APInt(C)))) ||
2365  !InstCombiner::isSignBitCheck(Pred, *C, IsTrueIfSignSet) ||
2366  X->getType() != SelType)
2367  return nullptr;
2368 
2369  // If needed, negate the value that will be the sign argument of the copysign:
2370  // (bitcast X) < 0 ? -TC : TC --> copysign(TC, X)
2371  // (bitcast X) < 0 ? TC : -TC --> copysign(TC, -X)
2372  // (bitcast X) >= 0 ? -TC : TC --> copysign(TC, -X)
2373  // (bitcast X) >= 0 ? TC : -TC --> copysign(TC, X)
2374  // Note: FMF from the select can not be propagated to the new instructions.
2375  if (IsTrueIfSignSet ^ TC->isNegative())
2376  X = Builder.CreateFNeg(X);
2377 
2378  // Canonicalize the magnitude argument as the positive constant since we do
2379  // not care about its sign.
2380  Value *MagArg = ConstantFP::get(SelType, abs(*TC));
2381  Function *F = Intrinsic::getDeclaration(Sel.getModule(), Intrinsic::copysign,
2382  Sel.getType());
2383  return CallInst::Create(F, { MagArg, X });
2384 }

2386 Instruction *InstCombinerImpl::foldVectorSelect(SelectInst &Sel) {
2387  if (!isa<VectorType>(Sel.getType()))
2388  return nullptr;
2389 
2390  Value *Cond = Sel.getCondition();
2391  Value *TVal = Sel.getTrueValue();
2392  Value *FVal = Sel.getFalseValue();
2393  Value *C, *X, *Y;
2394 
2395  if (match(Cond, m_VecReverse(m_Value(C)))) {
2396  auto createSelReverse = [&](Value *C, Value *X, Value *Y) {
2397  Value *V = Builder.CreateSelect(C, X, Y, Sel.getName(), &Sel);
2398  if (auto *I = dyn_cast<Instruction>(V))
2399  I->copyIRFlags(&Sel);
2400  Module *M = Sel.getModule();
2401  Function *F = Intrinsic::getDeclaration(
2402  M, Intrinsic::experimental_vector_reverse, V->getType());
2403  return CallInst::Create(F, V);
2404  };
2405 
2406  if (match(TVal, m_VecReverse(m_Value(X)))) {
2407  // select rev(C), rev(X), rev(Y) --> rev(select C, X, Y)
2408  if (match(FVal, m_VecReverse(m_Value(Y))) &&
2409  (Cond->hasOneUse() || TVal->hasOneUse() || FVal->hasOneUse()))
2410  return createSelReverse(C, X, Y);
2411 
2412  // select rev(C), rev(X), FValSplat --> rev(select C, X, FValSplat)
2413  if ((Cond->hasOneUse() || TVal->hasOneUse()) && isSplatValue(FVal))
2414  return createSelReverse(C, X, FVal);
2415  }
2416  // select rev(C), TValSplat, rev(Y) --> rev(select C, TValSplat, Y)
2417  else if (isSplatValue(TVal) && match(FVal, m_VecReverse(m_Value(Y))) &&
2418  (Cond->hasOneUse() || FVal->hasOneUse()))
2419  return createSelReverse(C, TVal, Y);
2420  }
2421 
2422  auto *VecTy = dyn_cast<FixedVectorType>(Sel.getType());
2423  if (!VecTy)
2424  return nullptr;
2425 
2426  unsigned NumElts = VecTy->getNumElements();
2427  APInt UndefElts(NumElts, 0);
2428  APInt AllOnesEltMask(APInt::getAllOnes(NumElts));
2429  if (Value *V = SimplifyDemandedVectorElts(&Sel, AllOnesEltMask, UndefElts)) {
2430  if (V != &Sel)
2431  return replaceInstUsesWith(Sel, V);
2432  return &Sel;
2433  }
2434 
2435  // A select of a "select shuffle" with a common operand can be rearranged
2436  // to select followed by "select shuffle". Because of poison, this only works
2437  // in the case of a shuffle with no undefined mask elements.
2438  ArrayRef<int> Mask;
2439  if (match(TVal, m_OneUse(m_Shuffle(m_Value(X), m_Value(Y), m_Mask(Mask)))) &&
2440  !is_contained(Mask, UndefMaskElem) &&
2441  cast<ShuffleVectorInst>(TVal)->isSelect()) {
2442  if (X == FVal) {
2443  // select Cond, (shuf_sel X, Y), X --> shuf_sel X, (select Cond, Y, X)
2444  Value *NewSel = Builder.CreateSelect(Cond, Y, X, "sel", &Sel);
2445  return new ShuffleVectorInst(X, NewSel, Mask);
2446  }
2447  if (Y == FVal) {
2448  // select Cond, (shuf_sel X, Y), Y --> shuf_sel (select Cond, X, Y), Y
2449  Value *NewSel = Builder.CreateSelect(Cond, X, Y, "sel", &Sel);
2450  return new ShuffleVectorInst(NewSel, Y, Mask);
2451  }
2452  }
2453  if (match(FVal, m_OneUse(m_Shuffle(m_Value(X), m_Value(Y), m_Mask(Mask)))) &&
2454  !is_contained(Mask, UndefMaskElem) &&
2455  cast<ShuffleVectorInst>(FVal)->isSelect()) {
2456  if (X == TVal) {
2457  // select Cond, X, (shuf_sel X, Y) --> shuf_sel X, (select Cond, X, Y)
2458  Value *NewSel = Builder.CreateSelect(Cond, X, Y, "sel", &Sel);
2459  return new ShuffleVectorInst(X, NewSel, Mask);
2460  }
2461  if (Y == TVal) {
2462  // select Cond, Y, (shuf_sel X, Y) --> shuf_sel (select Cond, Y, X), Y
2463  Value *NewSel = Builder.CreateSelect(Cond, Y, X, "sel", &Sel);
2464  return new ShuffleVectorInst(NewSel, Y, Mask);
2465  }
2466  }
2467 
2468  return nullptr;
2469 }

2471 static Instruction *foldSelectToPhiImpl(SelectInst &Sel, BasicBlock *BB,
2472  const DominatorTree &DT,
2473  InstCombiner::BuilderTy &Builder) {
2474  // Find the block's immediate dominator that ends with a conditional branch
2475  // that matches select's condition (maybe inverted).
2476  auto *IDomNode = DT[BB]->getIDom();
2477  if (!IDomNode)
2478  return nullptr;
2479  BasicBlock *IDom = IDomNode->getBlock();
2480 
2481  Value *Cond = Sel.getCondition();
2482  Value *IfTrue, *IfFalse;
2483  BasicBlock *TrueSucc, *FalseSucc;
2484  if (match(IDom->getTerminator(),
2485  m_Br(m_Specific(Cond), m_BasicBlock(TrueSucc),
2486  m_BasicBlock(FalseSucc)))) {
2487  IfTrue = Sel.getTrueValue();
2488  IfFalse = Sel.getFalseValue();
2489  } else if (match(IDom->getTerminator(),
2490  m_Br(m_Not(m_Specific(Cond)), m_BasicBlock(TrueSucc),
2491  m_BasicBlock(FalseSucc)))) {
2492  IfTrue = Sel.getFalseValue();
2493  IfFalse = Sel.getTrueValue();
2494  } else
2495  return nullptr;
2496 
2497  // Make sure the branches are actually different.
2498  if (TrueSucc == FalseSucc)
2499  return nullptr;
2500 
2501  // We want to replace select %cond, %a, %b with a phi that takes value %a
2502  // for all incoming edges that are dominated by condition `%cond == true`,
2503  // and value %b for edges dominated by condition `%cond == false`. If %a
2504  // or %b are also phis from the same basic block, we can go further and take
2505  // their incoming values from the corresponding blocks.
2506  BasicBlockEdge TrueEdge(IDom, TrueSucc);
2507  BasicBlockEdge FalseEdge(IDom, FalseSucc);
2508  DenseMap<BasicBlock *, Value *> Inputs;
2509  for (auto *Pred : predecessors(BB)) {
2510  // Check implication.
2511  BasicBlockEdge Incoming(Pred, BB);
2512  if (DT.dominates(TrueEdge, Incoming))
2513  Inputs[Pred] = IfTrue->DoPHITranslation(BB, Pred);
2514  else if (DT.dominates(FalseEdge, Incoming))
2515  Inputs[Pred] = IfFalse->DoPHITranslation(BB, Pred);
2516  else
2517  return nullptr;
2518  // Check availability.
2519  if (auto *Insn = dyn_cast<Instruction>(Inputs[Pred]))
2520  if (!DT.dominates(Insn, Pred->getTerminator()))
2521  return nullptr;
2522  }
2523 
2524  Builder.SetInsertPoint(&*BB->begin());
2525  auto *PN = Builder.CreatePHI(Sel.getType(), Inputs.size());
2526  for (auto *Pred : predecessors(BB))
2527  PN->addIncoming(Inputs[Pred], Pred);
2528  PN->takeName(&Sel);
2529  return PN;
2530 }

2532 static Instruction *foldSelectToPhi(SelectInst &Sel, const DominatorTree &DT,
2533  InstCombiner::BuilderTy &Builder) {
2534  // Try to replace this select with Phi in one of these blocks.
2535  SmallSetVector<BasicBlock *, 4> CandidateBlocks;
2536  CandidateBlocks.insert(Sel.getParent());
2537  for (Value *V : Sel.operands())
2538  if (auto *I = dyn_cast<Instruction>(V))
2539  CandidateBlocks.insert(I->getParent());
2540 
2541  for (BasicBlock *BB : CandidateBlocks)
2542  if (auto *PN = foldSelectToPhiImpl(Sel, BB, DT, Builder))
2543  return PN;
2544  return nullptr;

2547 static Value *foldSelectWithFrozenICmp(SelectInst &Sel, InstCombiner::BuilderTy &Builder) {
2548  FreezeInst *FI = dyn_cast<FreezeInst>(Sel.getCondition());
2549  if (!FI)
2550  return nullptr;
2551 
2552  Value *Cond = FI->getOperand(0);
2553  Value *TrueVal = Sel.getTrueValue(), *FalseVal = Sel.getFalseValue();
2554 
2555  // select (freeze(x == y)), x, y --> y
2556  // select (freeze(x != y)), x, y --> x
2557  // The freeze should be only used by this select. Otherwise, remaining uses of
2558  // the freeze can observe a contradictory value.
2559  // c = freeze(x == y) ; Let's assume that y = poison & x = 42; c is 0 or 1
2560  // a = select c, x, y ;
2561  // f(a, c) ; f(poison, 1) cannot happen, but if a is folded
2562  // ; to y, this can happen.
2563  CmpInst::Predicate Pred;
2564  if (FI->hasOneUse() &&
2565  match(Cond, m_c_ICmp(Pred, m_Specific(TrueVal), m_Specific(FalseVal))) &&
2566  (Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_EQ || Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_NE)) {
2567  return Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_EQ ? FalseVal : TrueVal;
2568  }
2569 
2570  return nullptr;
2571 }

2573 Instruction *InstCombinerImpl::foldAndOrOfSelectUsingImpliedCond(Value *Op,
2574  SelectInst &SI,
2575  bool IsAnd) {
2576  Value *CondVal = SI.getCondition();
2577  Value *A = SI.getTrueValue();
2578  Value *B = SI.getFalseValue();
2579 
2580  assert(Op->getType()->isIntOrIntVectorTy(1) &&
2581  "Op must be either i1 or vector of i1.");
2582 
2583  std::optional<bool> Res = isImpliedCondition(Op, CondVal, DL, IsAnd);
2584  if (!Res)
2585  return nullptr;
2586 
2587  Value *Zero = Constant::getNullValue(A->getType());
2588  Value *One = Constant::getAllOnesValue(A->getType());
2589 
2590  if (*Res == true) {
2591  if (IsAnd)
2592  // select op, (select cond, A, B), false => select op, A, false
2593  // and op, (select cond, A, B) => select op, A, false
2594  // if op = true implies condval = true.
2595  return SelectInst::Create(Op, A, Zero);
2596  else
2597  // select op, true, (select cond, A, B) => select op, true, A
2598  // or op, (select cond, A, B) => select op, true, A
2599  // if op = false implies condval = true.
2600  return SelectInst::Create(Op, One, A);
2601  } else {
2602  if (IsAnd)
2603  // select op, (select cond, A, B), false => select op, B, false
2604  // and op, (select cond, A, B) => select op, B, false
2605  // if op = true implies condval = false.
2606  return SelectInst::Create(Op, B, Zero);
2607  else
2608  // select op, true, (select cond, A, B) => select op, true, B
2609  // or op, (select cond, A, B) => select op, true, B
2610  // if op = false implies condval = false.
2611  return SelectInst::Create(Op, One, B);
2612  }
2613 }

2615 // Canonicalize select with fcmp to fabs(). -0.0 makes this tricky. We need
2616 // fast-math-flags (nsz) or fsub with +0.0 (not fneg) for this to work.
2617 static Instruction *foldSelectWithFCmpToFabs(SelectInst &SI,
2618  InstCombinerImpl &IC) {
2619  Value *CondVal = SI.getCondition();
2620 
2621  bool ChangedFMF = false;
2622  for (bool Swap : {false, true}) {
2623  Value *TrueVal = SI.getTrueValue();
2624  Value *X = SI.getFalseValue();
2625  CmpInst::Predicate Pred;
2626 
2627  if (Swap)
2628  std::swap(TrueVal, X);
2629 
2630  if (!match(CondVal, m_FCmp(Pred, m_Specific(X), m_AnyZeroFP())))
2631  continue;
2632 
2633  // fold (X <= +/-0.0) ? (0.0 - X) : X to fabs(X), when 'Swap' is false
2634  // fold (X > +/-0.0) ? X : (0.0 - X) to fabs(X), when 'Swap' is true
2635  if (match(TrueVal, m_FSub(m_PosZeroFP(), m_Specific(X)))) {
2636  if (!Swap && (Pred == FCmpInst::FCMP_OLE || Pred == FCmpInst::FCMP_ULE)) {
2637  Value *Fabs = IC.Builder.CreateUnaryIntrinsic(Intrinsic::fabs, X, &SI);
2638  return IC.replaceInstUsesWith(SI, Fabs);
2639  }
2640  if (Swap && (Pred == FCmpInst::FCMP_OGT || Pred == FCmpInst::FCMP_UGT)) {
2641  Value *Fabs = IC.Builder.CreateUnaryIntrinsic(Intrinsic::fabs, X, &SI);
2642  return IC.replaceInstUsesWith(SI, Fabs);
2643  }
2644  }
2645 
2646  if (!match(TrueVal, m_FNeg(m_Specific(X))))
2647  return nullptr;
2648 
2649  // Forward-propagate nnan and ninf from the fneg to the select.
2650  // If all inputs are not those values, then the select is not either.
2651  // Note: nsz is defined differently, so it may not be correct to propagate.
2652  FastMathFlags FMF = cast<FPMathOperator>(TrueVal)->getFastMathFlags();
2653  if (FMF.noNaNs() && !SI.hasNoNaNs()) {
2654  SI.setHasNoNaNs(true);
2655  ChangedFMF = true;
2656  }
2657  if (FMF.noInfs() && !SI.hasNoInfs()) {
2658  SI.setHasNoInfs(true);
2659  ChangedFMF = true;
2660  }
2661 
2662  // With nsz, when 'Swap' is false:
2663  // fold (X < +/-0.0) ? -X : X or (X <= +/-0.0) ? -X : X to fabs(X)
2664  // fold (X > +/-0.0) ? -X : X or (X >= +/-0.0) ? -X : X to -fabs(x)
2665  // when 'Swap' is true:
2666  // fold (X > +/-0.0) ? X : -X or (X >= +/-0.0) ? X : -X to fabs(X)
2667  // fold (X < +/-0.0) ? X : -X or (X <= +/-0.0) ? X : -X to -fabs(X)
2668  //
2669  // Note: We require "nnan" for this fold because fcmp ignores the signbit
2670  // of NAN, but IEEE-754 specifies the signbit of NAN values with
2671  // fneg/fabs operations.
2672  if (!SI.hasNoSignedZeros() || !SI.hasNoNaNs())
2673  return nullptr;
2674 
2675  if (Swap)
2676  Pred = FCmpInst::getSwappedPredicate(Pred);
2677 
2678  bool IsLTOrLE = Pred == FCmpInst::FCMP_OLT || Pred == FCmpInst::FCMP_OLE ||
2679  Pred == FCmpInst::FCMP_ULT || Pred == FCmpInst::FCMP_ULE;
2680  bool IsGTOrGE = Pred == FCmpInst::FCMP_OGT || Pred == FCmpInst::FCMP_OGE ||
2681  Pred == FCmpInst::FCMP_UGT || Pred == FCmpInst::FCMP_UGE;
2682 
2683  if (IsLTOrLE) {
2684  Value *Fabs = IC.Builder.CreateUnaryIntrinsic(Intrinsic::fabs, X, &SI);
2685  return IC.replaceInstUsesWith(SI, Fabs);
2686  }
2687  if (IsGTOrGE) {
2688  Value *Fabs = IC.Builder.CreateUnaryIntrinsic(Intrinsic::fabs, X, &SI);
2689  Instruction *NewFNeg = UnaryOperator::CreateFNeg(Fabs);
2690  NewFNeg->setFastMathFlags(SI.getFastMathFlags());
2691  return NewFNeg;
2692  }
2693  }
2694 
2695  return ChangedFMF ? &SI : nullptr;
2696 }

2698 // Match the following IR pattern:
2699 // %x.lowbits = and i8 %x, %lowbitmask
2700 // %x.lowbits.are.zero = icmp eq i8 %x.lowbits, 0
2701 // %x.biased = add i8 %x, %bias
2702 // %x.biased.highbits = and i8 %x.biased, %highbitmask
2703 // %x.roundedup = select i1 %x.lowbits.are.zero, i8 %x, i8 %x.biased.highbits
2704 // Define:
2705 // %alignment = add i8 %lowbitmask, 1
2706 // Iff 1. an %alignment is a power-of-two (aka, %lowbitmask is a low bit mask)
2707 // and 2. %bias is equal to either %lowbitmask or %alignment,
2708 // and 3. %highbitmask is equal to ~%lowbitmask (aka, to -%alignment)
2709 // then this pattern can be transformed into:
2710 // %x.offset = add i8 %x, %lowbitmask
2711 // %x.roundedup = and i8 %x.offset, %highbitmask
2712 static Value *
2713 foldRoundUpIntegerWithPow2Alignment(SelectInst &SI,
2714  InstCombiner::BuilderTy &Builder) {
2715  Value *Cond = SI.getCondition();
2716  Value *X = SI.getTrueValue();
2717  Value *XBiasedHighBits = SI.getFalseValue();
2718 
2719  ICmpInst::Predicate Pred;
2720  Value *XLowBits;
2721  if (!match(Cond, m_ICmp(Pred, m_Value(XLowBits), m_ZeroInt())) ||
2722  !ICmpInst::isEquality(Pred))
2723  return nullptr;
2724 
2725  if (Pred == ICmpInst::Predicate::ICMP_NE)
2726  std::swap(X, XBiasedHighBits);
2727 
2728  // FIXME: we could support non non-splats here.
2729 
2730  const APInt *LowBitMaskCst;
2731  if (!match(XLowBits, m_And(m_Specific(X), m_APIntAllowUndef(LowBitMaskCst))))
2732  return nullptr;
2733 
2734  // Match even if the AND and ADD are swapped.
2735  const APInt *BiasCst, *HighBitMaskCst;
2736  if (!match(XBiasedHighBits,
2737  m_And(m_Add(m_Specific(X), m_APIntAllowUndef(BiasCst)),
2738  m_APIntAllowUndef(HighBitMaskCst))) &&
2739  !match(XBiasedHighBits,
2740  m_Add(m_And(m_Specific(X), m_APIntAllowUndef(HighBitMaskCst)),
2741  m_APIntAllowUndef(BiasCst))))
2742  return nullptr;
2743 
2744  if (!LowBitMaskCst->isMask())
2745  return nullptr;
2746 
2747  APInt InvertedLowBitMaskCst = ~*LowBitMaskCst;
2748  if (InvertedLowBitMaskCst != *HighBitMaskCst)
2749  return nullptr;
2750 
2751  APInt AlignmentCst = *LowBitMaskCst + 1;
2752 
2753  if (*BiasCst != AlignmentCst && *BiasCst != *LowBitMaskCst)
2754  return nullptr;
2755 
2756  if (!XBiasedHighBits->hasOneUse()) {
2757  if (*BiasCst == *LowBitMaskCst)
2758  return XBiasedHighBits;
2759  return nullptr;
2760  }
2761 
2762  // FIXME: could we preserve undef's here?
2763  Type *Ty = X->getType();
2764  Value *XOffset = Builder.CreateAdd(X, ConstantInt::get(Ty, *LowBitMaskCst),
2765  X->getName() + ".biased");
2766  Value *R = Builder.CreateAnd(XOffset, ConstantInt::get(Ty, *HighBitMaskCst));
2767  R->takeName(&SI);
2768  return R;
2769 }

2771 namespace {
2772 struct DecomposedSelect {
2773  Value *Cond = nullptr;
2774  Value *TrueVal = nullptr;
2775  Value *FalseVal = nullptr;
2776 };
2777 } // namespace
2778 
2779 /// Look for patterns like
2780 /// %outer.cond = select i1 %inner.cond, i1 %alt.cond, i1 false
2781 /// %inner.sel = select i1 %inner.cond, i8 %inner.sel.t, i8 %inner.sel.f
2782 /// %outer.sel = select i1 %outer.cond, i8 %outer.sel.t, i8 %inner.sel
2783 /// and rewrite it as
2784 /// %inner.sel = select i1 %cond.alternative, i8 %sel.outer.t, i8 %sel.inner.t
2785 /// %sel.outer = select i1 %cond.inner, i8 %inner.sel, i8 %sel.inner.f
2786 static Instruction *foldNestedSelects(SelectInst &OuterSelVal,
2787  InstCombiner::BuilderTy &Builder) {
2788  // We must start with a `select`.
2789  DecomposedSelect OuterSel;
2790  match(&OuterSelVal,
2791  m_Select(m_Value(OuterSel.Cond), m_Value(OuterSel.TrueVal),
2792  m_Value(OuterSel.FalseVal)));
2793 
2794  // Canonicalize inversion of the outermost `select`'s condition.
2795  if (match(OuterSel.Cond, m_Not(m_Value(OuterSel.Cond))))
2796  std::swap(OuterSel.TrueVal, OuterSel.FalseVal);
2797 
2798  // The condition of the outermost select must be an `and`/`or`.
2799  if (!match(OuterSel.Cond, m_c_LogicalOp(m_Value(), m_Value())))
2800  return nullptr;
2801 
2802  // Depending on the logical op, inner select might be in different hand.
2803  bool IsAndVariant = match(OuterSel.Cond, m_LogicalAnd());
2804  Value *InnerSelVal = IsAndVariant ? OuterSel.FalseVal : OuterSel.TrueVal;
2805 
2806  // Profitability check - avoid increasing instruction count.
2807  if (none_of(ArrayRef<Value *>({OuterSelVal.getCondition(), InnerSelVal}),
2808  [](Value *V) { return V->hasOneUse(); }))
2809  return nullptr;
2810 
2811  // The appropriate hand of the outermost `select` must be a select itself.
2812  DecomposedSelect InnerSel;
2813  if (!match(InnerSelVal,
2814  m_Select(m_Value(InnerSel.Cond), m_Value(InnerSel.TrueVal),
2815  m_Value(InnerSel.FalseVal))))
2816  return nullptr;
2817 
2818  // Canonicalize inversion of the innermost `select`'s condition.
2819  if (match(InnerSel.Cond, m_Not(m_Value(InnerSel.Cond))))
2820  std::swap(InnerSel.TrueVal, InnerSel.FalseVal);
2821 
2822  Value *AltCond = nullptr;
2823  auto matchOuterCond = [OuterSel, &AltCond](auto m_InnerCond) {
2824  return match(OuterSel.Cond, m_c_LogicalOp(m_InnerCond, m_Value(AltCond)));
2825  };
2826 
2827  // Finally, match the condition that was driving the outermost `select`,
2828  // it should be a logical operation between the condition that was driving
2829  // the innermost `select` (after accounting for the possible inversions
2830  // of the condition), and some other condition.
2831  if (matchOuterCond(m_Specific(InnerSel.Cond))) {
2832  // Done!
2833  } else if (Value * NotInnerCond; matchOuterCond(m_CombineAnd(
2834  m_Not(m_Specific(InnerSel.Cond)), m_Value(NotInnerCond)))) {
2835  // Done!
2836  std::swap(InnerSel.TrueVal, InnerSel.FalseVal);
2837  InnerSel.Cond = NotInnerCond;
2838  } else // Not the pattern we were looking for.
2839  return nullptr;
2840 
2841  Value *SelInner = Builder.CreateSelect(
2842  AltCond, IsAndVariant ? OuterSel.TrueVal : InnerSel.FalseVal,
2843  IsAndVariant ? InnerSel.TrueVal : OuterSel.FalseVal);
2844  SelInner->takeName(InnerSelVal);
2845  return SelectInst::Create(InnerSel.Cond,
2846  IsAndVariant ? SelInner : InnerSel.TrueVal,
2847  !IsAndVariant ? SelInner : InnerSel.FalseVal);
2848 }

2850 Instruction *InstCombinerImpl::foldSelectOfBools(SelectInst &SI) {
2851  Value *CondVal = SI.getCondition();
2852  Value *TrueVal = SI.getTrueValue();
2853  Value *FalseVal = SI.getFalseValue();
2854  Type *SelType = SI.getType();
2855 
2856  // Avoid potential infinite loops by checking for non-constant condition.
2857  // TODO: Can we assert instead by improving canonicalizeSelectToShuffle()?
2858  // Scalar select must have simplified?
2859  if (!SelType->isIntOrIntVectorTy(1) || isa<Constant>(CondVal) ||
2860  TrueVal->getType() != CondVal->getType())
2861  return nullptr;
2862 
2863  auto *One = ConstantInt::getTrue(SelType);
2864  auto *Zero = ConstantInt::getFalse(SelType);
2865  Value *A, *B, *C, *D;
2866 
2867  // Folding select to and/or i1 isn't poison safe in general. impliesPoison
2868  // checks whether folding it does not convert a well-defined value into
2869  // poison.
2870  if (match(TrueVal, m_One())) {
2871  if (impliesPoison(FalseVal, CondVal)) {
2872  // Change: A = select B, true, C --> A = or B, C
2873  return BinaryOperator::CreateOr(CondVal, FalseVal);
2874  }
2875 
2876  if (auto *LHS = dyn_cast<FCmpInst>(CondVal))
2877  if (auto *RHS = dyn_cast<FCmpInst>(FalseVal))
2878  if (Value *V = foldLogicOfFCmps(LHS, RHS, /*IsAnd*/ false,
2879  /*IsSelectLogical*/ true))
2880  return replaceInstUsesWith(SI, V);
2881 
2882  // (A && B) || (C && B) --> (A || C) && B
2883  if (match(CondVal, m_LogicalAnd(m_Value(A), m_Value(B))) &&
2884  match(FalseVal, m_LogicalAnd(m_Value(C), m_Value(D))) &&
2885  (CondVal->hasOneUse() || FalseVal->hasOneUse())) {
2886  bool CondLogicAnd = isa<SelectInst>(CondVal);
2887  bool FalseLogicAnd = isa<SelectInst>(FalseVal);
2888  auto AndFactorization = [&](Value *Common, Value *InnerCond,
2889  Value *InnerVal,
2890  bool SelFirst = false) -> Instruction * {
2891  Value *InnerSel = Builder.CreateSelect(InnerCond, One, InnerVal);
2892  if (SelFirst)
2893  std::swap(Common, InnerSel);
2894  if (FalseLogicAnd || (CondLogicAnd && Common == A))
2895  return SelectInst::Create(Common, InnerSel, Zero);
2896  else
2897  return BinaryOperator::CreateAnd(Common, InnerSel);
2898  };
2899 
2900  if (A == C)
2901  return AndFactorization(A, B, D);
2902  if (A == D)
2903  return AndFactorization(A, B, C);
2904  if (B == C)
2905  return AndFactorization(B, A, D);
2906  if (B == D)
2907  return AndFactorization(B, A, C, CondLogicAnd && FalseLogicAnd);
2908  }
2909  }
2910 
2911  if (match(FalseVal, m_Zero())) {
2912  if (impliesPoison(TrueVal, CondVal)) {
2913  // Change: A = select B, C, false --> A = and B, C
2914  return BinaryOperator::CreateAnd(CondVal, TrueVal);
2915  }
2916 
2917  if (auto *LHS = dyn_cast<FCmpInst>(CondVal))
2918  if (auto *RHS = dyn_cast<FCmpInst>(TrueVal))
2919  if (Value *V = foldLogicOfFCmps(LHS, RHS, /*IsAnd*/ true,
2920  /*IsSelectLogical*/ true))
2921  return replaceInstUsesWith(SI, V);
2922 
2923  // (A || B) && (C || B) --> (A && C) || B
2924  if (match(CondVal, m_LogicalOr(m_Value(A), m_Value(B))) &&
2925  match(TrueVal, m_LogicalOr(m_Value(C), m_Value(D))) &&
2926  (CondVal->hasOneUse() || TrueVal->hasOneUse())) {
2927  bool CondLogicOr = isa<SelectInst>(CondVal);
2928  bool TrueLogicOr = isa<SelectInst>(TrueVal);
2929  auto OrFactorization = [&](Value *Common, Value *InnerCond,
2930  Value *InnerVal,
2931  bool SelFirst = false) -> Instruction * {
2932  Value *InnerSel = Builder.CreateSelect(InnerCond, InnerVal, Zero);
2933  if (SelFirst)
2934  std::swap(Common, InnerSel);
2935  if (TrueLogicOr || (CondLogicOr && Common == A))
2936  return SelectInst::Create(Common, One, InnerSel);
2937  else
2938  return BinaryOperator::CreateOr(Common, InnerSel);
2939  };
2940 
2941  if (A == C)
2942  return OrFactorization(A, B, D);
2943  if (A == D)
2944  return OrFactorization(A, B, C);
2945  if (B == C)
2946  return OrFactorization(B, A, D);
2947  if (B == D)
2948  return OrFactorization(B, A, C, CondLogicOr && TrueLogicOr);
2949  }
2950  }
2951 
2952  // We match the "full" 0 or 1 constant here to avoid a potential infinite
2953  // loop with vectors that may have undefined/poison elements.
2954  // select a, false, b -> select !a, b, false
2955  if (match(TrueVal, m_Specific(Zero))) {
2956  Value *NotCond = Builder.CreateNot(CondVal, "not." + CondVal->getName());
2957  return SelectInst::Create(NotCond, FalseVal, Zero);
2958  }
2959  // select a, b, true -> select !a, true, b
2960  if (match(FalseVal, m_Specific(One))) {
2961  Value *NotCond = Builder.CreateNot(CondVal, "not." + CondVal->getName());
2962  return SelectInst::Create(NotCond, One, TrueVal);
2963  }
2964 
2965  // DeMorgan in select form: !a && !b --> !(a || b)
2966  // select !a, !b, false --> not (select a, true, b)
2967  if (match(&SI, m_LogicalAnd(m_Not(m_Value(A)), m_Not(m_Value(B)))) &&
2968  (CondVal->hasOneUse() || TrueVal->hasOneUse()) &&
2969  !match(A, m_ConstantExpr()) && !match(B, m_ConstantExpr()))
2970  return BinaryOperator::CreateNot(Builder.CreateSelect(A, One, B));
2971 
2972  // DeMorgan in select form: !a || !b --> !(a && b)
2973  // select !a, true, !b --> not (select a, b, false)
2974  if (match(&SI, m_LogicalOr(m_Not(m_Value(A)), m_Not(m_Value(B)))) &&
2975  (CondVal->hasOneUse() || FalseVal->hasOneUse()) &&
2976  !match(A, m_ConstantExpr()) && !match(B, m_ConstantExpr()))
2977  return BinaryOperator::CreateNot(Builder.CreateSelect(A, B, Zero));
2978 
2979  // select (select a, true, b), true, b -> select a, true, b
2980  if (match(CondVal, m_Select(m_Value(A), m_One(), m_Value(B))) &&
2981  match(TrueVal, m_One()) && match(FalseVal, m_Specific(B)))
2982  return replaceOperand(SI, 0, A);
2983  // select (select a, b, false), b, false -> select a, b, false
2984  if (match(CondVal, m_Select(m_Value(A), m_Value(B), m_Zero())) &&
2985  match(TrueVal, m_Specific(B)) && match(FalseVal, m_Zero()))
2986  return replaceOperand(SI, 0, A);
2987 
2988  // ~(A & B) & (A | B) --> A ^ B
2989  if (match(&SI, m_c_LogicalAnd(m_Not(m_LogicalAnd(m_Value(A), m_Value(B))),
2990  m_c_LogicalOr(m_Deferred(A), m_Deferred(B)))))
2991  return BinaryOperator::CreateXor(A, B);
2992 
2993  // select (~a | c), a, b -> and a, (or c, freeze(b))
2994  if (match(CondVal, m_c_Or(m_Not(m_Specific(TrueVal)), m_Value(C))) &&
2995  CondVal->hasOneUse()) {
2996  FalseVal = Builder.CreateFreeze(FalseVal);
2997  return BinaryOperator::CreateAnd(TrueVal, Builder.CreateOr(C, FalseVal));
2998  }
2999  // select (~c & b), a, b -> and b, (or freeze(a), c)
3000  if (match(CondVal, m_c_And(m_Not(m_Value(C)), m_Specific(FalseVal))) &&
3001  CondVal->hasOneUse()) {
3002  TrueVal = Builder.CreateFreeze(TrueVal);
3003  return BinaryOperator::CreateAnd(FalseVal, Builder.CreateOr(C, TrueVal));
3004  }
3005 
3006  if (match(FalseVal, m_Zero()) || match(TrueVal, m_One())) {
3007  Use *Y = nullptr;

3012  InsertNewInstBefore(FI, *cast<Instruction>(Y->getUser()));

3030  // select c, (a || b), false -> select c, a, false
3031  // if c implies that b is false.
3032  if (match(CondVal, m_LogicalOr(m_Value(A), m_Value(B))) &&

3037  }

3039  match(FalseVal, m_Zero())) {
3040  std::optional<bool> Res = isImpliedCondition(CondVal, B, DL);
3041  if (Res && *Res == false)
3042  return replaceOperand(SI, 1, A);
3043  }
3044  // select c, true, (a && b) -> select c, true, a
3045  // select (a && b), true, c -> select a, true, c
3046  // if c = false implies that b = true
3047  if (match(TrueVal, m_One()) &&
3048  match(FalseVal, m_LogicalAnd(m_Value(A), m_Value(B)))) {
3049  std::optional<bool> Res = isImpliedCondition(CondVal, B, DL, false);
3050  if (Res && *Res == true)
3051  return replaceOperand(SI, 2, A);
3052  }
3053  if (match(CondVal, m_LogicalAnd(m_Value(A), m_Value(B))) &&
3054  match(TrueVal, m_One())) {
3055  std::optional<bool> Res = isImpliedCondition(FalseVal, B, DL, false);
3056  if (Res && *Res == true)
3057  return replaceOperand(SI, 0, A);
3058  }
3059 
3060  if (match(TrueVal, m_One())) {
3061  Value *C;
3062 
3063  // (C && A) || (!C && B) --> sel C, A, B
3064  // (A && C) || (!C && B) --> sel C, A, B
3065  // (C && A) || (B && !C) --> sel C, A, B
3066  // (A && C) || (B && !C) --> sel C, A, B (may require freeze)
3067  if (match(FalseVal, m_c_LogicalAnd(m_Not(m_Value(C)), m_Value(B))) &&
3068  match(CondVal, m_c_LogicalAnd(m_Specific(C), m_Value(A)))) {
3069  auto *SelCond = dyn_cast<SelectInst>(CondVal);
3070  auto *SelFVal = dyn_cast<SelectInst>(FalseVal);
3071  bool MayNeedFreeze = SelCond && SelFVal &&
3072  match(SelFVal->getTrueValue(),
3073  m_Not(m_Specific(SelCond->getTrueValue())));
3074  if (MayNeedFreeze)
3075  C = Builder.CreateFreeze(C);
3076  return SelectInst::Create(C, A, B);
3077  }
3078 
3079  // (!C && A) || (C && B) --> sel C, B, A
3080  // (A && !C) || (C && B) --> sel C, B, A
3081  // (!C && A) || (B && C) --> sel C, B, A
3082  // (A && !C) || (B && C) --> sel C, B, A (may require freeze)
3083  if (match(CondVal, m_c_LogicalAnd(m_Not(m_Value(C)), m_Value(A))) &&
3084  match(FalseVal, m_c_LogicalAnd(m_Specific(C), m_Value(B)))) {
3085  auto *SelCond = dyn_cast<SelectInst>(CondVal);
3086  auto *SelFVal = dyn_cast<SelectInst>(FalseVal);
3087  bool MayNeedFreeze = SelCond && SelFVal &&
3088  match(SelCond->getTrueValue(),
3089  m_Not(m_Specific(SelFVal->getTrueValue())));
3090  if (MayNeedFreeze)
3091  C = Builder.CreateFreeze(C);
3092  return SelectInst::Create(C, B, A);
3093  }
3094  }
3095 
3096  return nullptr;
3097 }

3501  MaskedInst->setArgOperand(3, FalseVal /* Zero */);
3502  return replaceInstUsesWith(SI, MaskedInst);
3503  }

3506  if (match(TrueVal, m_Zero()) &&
3507  (match(FalseVal, m_MaskedLoad(m_Value(), m_Value(), m_Value(Mask),
3508  m_CombineOr(m_Undef(), m_Zero()))) ||
3509  match(FalseVal, m_MaskedGather(m_Value(), m_Value(), m_Value(Mask),
3510  m_CombineOr(m_Undef(), m_Zero())))) &&

3512  // We can remove the select by ensuring the load zeros all lanes the
3513  // select would have. We determine this by proving there is no overlap
3514  // between the load and select masks.
3515  // (i.e (load_mask & select_mask) == 0 == no overlap)
3516  bool CanMergeSelectIntoLoad = false;
3517  if (Value *V = simplifyAndInst(CondVal, Mask, SQ.getWithInstruction(&SI)))
3518  CanMergeSelectIntoLoad = match(V, m_Zero());
3519

3522  if (isa<UndefValue>(MaskedInst->getArgOperand(3)))
3523  MaskedInst->setArgOperand(3, TrueVal /* Zero */);
3524  return replaceInstUsesWith(SI, MaskedInst);
3525  }
3526  }
3527 
3528  if (Instruction *I = foldNestedSelects(SI, Builder))
3529  return I;
3530 
3531  // Match logical variants of the pattern,
3532  // and transform them iff that gets rid of inversions.
3533  // (~x) | y --> ~(x & (~y))
3534  // (~x) & y --> ~(x | (~y))
3535  if (sinkNotIntoOtherHandOfLogicalOp(SI))
3536  return &SI;
3537 
3538  return nullptr;
